(189, 'KEzLV1I44Ishs6aGRJnp5hghlRpXYGaItZyfFYmZOZ', 'Choroi mallet 100~600', NULL, '7lRDbO', '82dc824b-de0a-ac43-ceab-aaab1d942afc', 'Admin', 580, 'room', NULL, 'dInJyt5owN2KjhCgxXCvltqfzQ5bNY8NLEflLl3h1T', '/photos/1/槌/20171229123423.jpg', '[]', '<p>貨號：55158888<br />\n<br />\nChoroi mallet 000~600<br />\nArticle number 55158xxx<br />\nFelt for aluminium and low pitched wood produces the softest tone.<br />\nSoft rubber for aluminium and low pitched wood produces a slightly stronger tone than felt.<br />\nHard rubber for brass and high pitched wood produces a slightly stronger tone than leather.<br />\nLeather for brass and high pitched wood produces a slightly milder tone than hard rubber.<br />\nWood for brass and high pitched wood produces a succinct, strong tone.<br />\n<br />\nLength: 32 cm (length: 12.6 inch), head diam. 30 mm (1.18 inch), 6 diff. materials available.<br />\n<br />\nMaterial:<br />\n55158000 felt<br />\n55158100 soft rubber<br />\n55158300 hard rubber<br />\n55158400 leather<br />\n55158500 wood, pent.<br />\n55158600 wood<br />\n<br />\nChoroi /單支</p>', '<p>貨號：55158888</p>', 'instock', 1, 1, 50, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '{\"weight\":null,\"size\":{\"productLength\":null,\"productWidth\":null,\"productHeight\":null}}', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2018-08-16 13:23:19', '2018-08-16 13:23:19'),
(190, 'Q67K75lAnRION0967GrPj0Hjji75V8qnpwY8tVSFAU', 'Graphite pencils B', NULL, 'wGLqMz', '82dc824b-de0a-ac43-ceab-aaab1d942afc', 'Admin', 180, 'room', NULL, 'YJqlhdKehJaWpMhdlKW1FKHKz0ClKqtRbcd42m2Ihw', '/photos/1/鉛筆(細)/20180104170143.jpg', '[]', '<p>貨號：20505011<br />\n<br />\n12支/紙盒 [B]</p>\n\n<p>模型：六角<br />\n<br />\n顏色：B<br />\n<br />\n尺寸：長175mm/直徑7mm</p>\n\n<p>Graphite pencils B<br />\n<br />\nArticle number 20505011</p>\n\n<p>These graphite pencils of a very high (artists / professional) quality, are produced by the renowned family business Koh-i-Noor Hartdmuth. This Czech company has been the worldwide leader of high quality products such as crayons, oil paint, charcoal, chalk, etc., for 225 years. They specialize in many levels of hardness?s. The hardness codes have been devised by the German Friedrich von Hardtmuth of this same Koh-I-Noor factory. He had thought that the H stands for hard (Hart in German), the B soft (Blei in German) and F (this is the current HB) for fine writing (Fein in German).</p>\n\n<p>We offer you these pencils in the range of 4B (very soft) to 4H (very hard), so you can draw whatever you like, draw lines, sketches, shades etc. With a 4H pencil, you may sign or draw on stone and metal material. The soft pencils give you the possibility to create the volatility of charcoal and you can make shadows and depths. The colouring of large surfaces is done with a soft pencil. With the hard pencils you can make very detailed work with sharp turns and glossy lines. A hard pencil is harder to erase then a soft pencil. The pencils HB and H are most suitable for writing.</p>\n\n<p>Graphite Pencils with a Soft Lead (B)<br />\nThe higher the number of B, the softer the lead. Suitable for, among other things, to create shadow and depth.</p>\n\n<p>Graphite Pencils with an average Hardness (HB)<br />\nSuitable for many purposes, including writing.</p>\n\n<p>Graphite Pencils with a Hard Lead (H)<br />\nThe higher the number of H, the harder the lead. Sui